title: Arizona Big Buckle
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Arizona is a genuine classic. Modeled on the cork sandal, this version is made from EVA. The high-quality, odor-neutral EVA has been tested for harmful substances and combines numerous positive attributes: it is very light, highly elastic, water-resistant, and skin-friendly and offers the comfort you have come to expect from BIRKENSTOCK. This version features our popular Big Buckle made from a stainless synthetic material and makes an impression with its durability and minimalist design. Anatomically shaped BIRKENSTOCK footbed made from EVA Upper/footbed lining/sole: a single piece of EVA Details: water-resistant, washable, ultra-lightweight Made in Germany EVA (ethylene vinyl acetate) is a high-quality, very light, elastic material with very good cushioning. As a result, it smooths out slight irregularities in the floor and ensures that every step is softly cushioned.

title: Arizona
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Arizona is a genuine classic that has been delighting both men and women with its timeless design for decades. Modeled on the cork original, this sandal is made from ultra lightweight and highly flexible EVA. This casual sneaker has an additional mid sole made of PU and cork to ensure optimum shock absorption. It also features a breathable microfiber lining for a comfortable foot climate. The upper is made of high-quality, soft natural leather. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: natural leather Footbed lining: natural leather Sole: rubber Made in Portugal The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Tokio ESD
description: The Tokio ESD offers the ideal combination of classic looks and reliable protection from electrostatic discharge. The ESD version therefore protects man and materials in highly sensitive areas like in the semiconductor industry. All BIRKENSTOCK ESD models are tested in accordance with the requirements of EN 61340 and meet the ESD requirements of 1.0 × 105 to 3.5 × 107 ohms. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed in an ESD version Upper: smooth leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA outsole in an ESD version Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckles ESD protection tested in accordance with EN 61340 The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Tokio PAP Chunky
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Tokio clog is a variation of the classic Boston. The model is characterized by its ankle strap and can easily be worn any time of the year. Here, Papillio presents the clog with a stylish platform sole with extra deep tread lines. The bevel results in maximum walking comfort. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed; exquisite Upper: natural leather Footbed lining: smooth leather Sole: EVA Heel type: platform; heel height: 30 mm Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckles Footbed “Made in Germany” The footbed liner and outer edge of the footbed of BIRKENSTOCK Exquisite models are wrapped in very soft and supple nappa leather.

title: Tokio PRO
description: The BIRKENSTOCK classic Tokio Pro has become a true classic among professional shoes, especially for medical professions. The clog is fitted with an anatomically shaped original BIRKENSTOCK cork-latex footbed and a dual-component sole. This comprises a cushioning midsole made from EVA and a nonslip, dynamic, treaded outsole made from genuine rubber. The outsole can furthermore be repaired. Therefore, the clog is particularly well suited to day-to-day wear in hospitals. The upper is made from high-quality, particularly soft natural leather which is coated with polyurethane (PU). The PU coating makes the material more durable and thus particularly long-lasting. The clog offers comfort and safety. The shoe’s enclosed design protects the foot from impacts and the injuries they cause. Thanks to the adjustable strap with a sturdy metal buckle on the instep, it can also be adjusted to the wearer’s feet. A backstrap that can be perfectly fitted to the wearer’s feet thanks to an individually adjustable metal buckle provides the foot with additional grip and a firm step – even when everyday working life gets hectic. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: PU-coated natural leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: super grip sole, slip-resistant rubber-EVA sole Tested for slip resistance (SRC category) in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckles The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Tokio Super Grip
description: With the Tokio Super Grip, BIRKENSTOCK developed a clog for occupations that demand a great deal of stamina from the wearers and their feet. Its Super Grip sole results in the ideal rolling motion and is nonslip. A midsole made from EVA cushions every step. The special rubber tread delivers tangible sure-footedness. This stability is further enhanced by the adjustable backstrap. This is something that’s appreciated by those working in the medical professions and in kitchens and by service staff, all of whom often spend hours on their feet. The sole of the Tokio Super Grip has been tested for slip resistance in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: smooth leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA midsole with nonslip, oil- and grease-resistant rubber outsole Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckles Slip resistance tested in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 (SRA category) The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Zürich 1964
description: Two in one! The BIRKENSTOCK Zürich combines the stability of an enclosed shoe with the lightness of a sandal. In our Anniversary Collection, we bring back this popular classic in its original design. With its buckles, footbed stamp, outsole and packaging , the sandal looks just like the original from 1964 and exudes real retro flair. The upper is made from especially soft suede which hugs the foot like a second skin. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: one strap with two individually adjustable metal pin buckles in their original design Made in Germany Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Zürich
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Zürich combines the stability of a closed-toe shoe with the lightness of a sandal and is popular in equal measure among both men and women. Although closed at the sides, this version is open at the toes and heel to ensure the feet get enough fresh air. This version boasts an authentic and rustic mix of materials featuring soft synthetic felt and thick natural leather. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: synthetic felt; natural leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: one strap with two individually adjustable metal pin buckles “Made in Germany” Natural leather can be recognized by its untreated surface. BIRKENSTOCK purposely does not treat surface grains and other characteristic features. BIRKENSTOCK uses sturdy leather with a thickness of 2.8 to 3.2 millimeters as upper material.

title: Gizeh Big Buckle
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Gizeh is a genuine classic and a stylish all-rounder. Our elegant thong sandal combines optimum grip with minimalist, fashionable design. title: Gizeh Soft Footbed
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Gizeh is a genuine classic that combines optimum grip with minimalist, fashionable design. This sandal was reinterpreted in an extravagant metallic look. The reflective film makes this classic model dazzle and is sure to make any outfit turn heads. With its additional foam layer, the soft footbed offers extra comfort and pampers feet – all day long. The upper is made from high-quality, soft natural leather. Original BIRKENSTOCK soft footbed; anatomically shaped Upper: natural leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: thong with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle; soft footbed “Made in Germany” The soft footbed has an integrated latex foam cushion. So it offers excellent comfort from day one.

title: Highwood Lace Low
description: The Highwood Low by BIRKENSTOCK is a simple, elegant low shoe with laces that is immediately recognizable as a BIRKENSTOCK original thanks to the integrated cork element in the sole. The comfortable and light Deep Blue Footbed makes the shoe a perfect 24/7 all-rounder, especially on long and active days. Perfect for your next holiday, extensive walks, or city trips. The upper is made from extra thick, oiled nubuck leather with an open-selvage finish. Original BIRKENSTOCK Deep Blue Footbed; anatomically shaped and removable Upper: oiled nubuck leather Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: natural rubber Made in Portugal Oiled leather is one of our favourite types of leather. Its oily waxed surface makes for a unique colour effect and develops a beautiful patina. The oily finish of our natural leather products results in colour variation, making each and every pair unique.

title: Kyoto
description: The casual BIRKENSTOCK Kyoto takes its inspiration from the classic Zürich model and stands out with its compact design and individually adjustable fastener. It offers optimum grip and is complemented by two decorative rivets. The shiny fasteners are sophisticated eye-catchers. The semi-exquisite footbed is fully lined with soft piumato leather, making it exceptionally comfortable. The upper made of soft, high-quality nubuck leather is complemented by accents of shiny patent leather. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed; semi-exquisite Upper: nubuck leather; natural leather with patent coating Footbed lining: piumato leather Sole: EVA Details: individually adjustable fastener Made in Germany Nubuck leather is the result of a gentle buffing of the top-grain layer of the hide. It is soft to the touch and develops a beautiful patina over time.

title: Arizona

title: Florida Flex Platform
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Florida is the ideal sandal for anyone who spends a lot of time on their feet. Here, Papillio presents the three-strap sandal with a trendy platform sole. The new platform flex outsole has a wider heel section for increased stability and ideal weight distribution. This popular sandal has been given an update in a new material, with a vegan version now available. It is entirely free of animal products, as verified by independent testing laboratories. The updated design with horizontal grooves in the front part improves flexibility and the rolling motion. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: flexible cork-latex sole Heel type: platform; 28 mm Details: three straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle Footbed made in Germany Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Naples
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Naples is the men’s version of the popular semi-open Buckley clog. The moccasin style with striking stitching lends this sandal a unique and masculine appearance. title: Rio Kids
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Rio is a sporty, elegant sandal with an ankle strap that offers reliable and comfortable grip – also during rough-and-tumble play. Here, we see the sandal with a silky sheen finish. The color-coordinated footbed rounds off the shoe’s look of sophistication. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. title: St Barths
description: With the St. Barths, BIRKENSTOCK presents a particularly sophisticated and feminine version of the classic Arizona. The two-part outsole facilitates the rolling of the foot and ensures an elegant gait. The premium rectangular zamak buckles with a convex shape perfectly fit the foot and embody a contemporary design. The exquisite footbed is fully lined with soft leather, making it exceptionally comfortable. The upper is made from high-quality, soft natural leather. title: Super Birki 2.0
description: The PU (polyurethane) clog Super Birki is suitable for leisure, garden, and professional wear. With its flat heel section, this popular and seamless clog provides the feet with all-around protection and grip. The flexible PU material with its smooth surface is water- and dirt-repellent, making the Super Birki extremely easy-care. The ergonomically designed cork footbed with its skin-friendly and breathable microfiber lining delivers a high level of comfort. This makes the Super Birki suitable for the wearer’s own personal insoles. The cork footbed is removable and can be washed at up to 30°C. The Super Birki (without footbed) can be washed at up to 80°C. BIRKENSTOCK also takes safety extremely seriously in terms of sole design: the directly foamed, flexible PU sole features a nonslip tread that offers firm grip on slippery surfaces (certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 OB E (SRC category)). Work shoe certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 OB E (SRC category) Replaceable, anatomically shaped cork footbed Upper: PU (polyurethane) Sole: PU, nonslip, oil- and grease-resistant Details: PU clog washable at up to 80°C, footbed at up to 30°C Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Super-Birki
description: The wide array of colors that the Super Birki is available in makes it highly versatile for use in all sorts of occupational and private settings. This compact shoe made from water-resistant and dirt-repellent polyurethane is also oil- and grease-resistant. This extremely resilient material is washable at up to 60° Celsius and can be efficiently disinfected. Its resilience and its hygiene properties make it ideal for kitchens, medical environments, and the food industry – while it can equally serve as a practical garden clog. The anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed is lined with a moisture-wicking fabric. It can be removed for easy cleaning and is washable at up to 30° Celsius. title: A630
description: The A 630 PU clog covers all bases when it comes to stringent hygiene standards and reliable nonslip properties. Its enclosed design and the nonslip treaded sole offer reliable grip and maximum sure-footedness in kitchens and the food industry. Its oil- and grease-resistant material is also water-resistant, allowing it to be cleaned efficiently and thoroughly. This involves removing the cork-latex footbed and washing the clog at up to 80° Celsius. Both parts of the shoe are suitable for daily disinfection. The anatomically shaped original BIRKENSTOCK footbed protects joints and tendons, and is also washable at up to 30° Celsius. The footbed is available separately and can therefore be replaced if necessary. The A 630 model is certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 OB E (SRC category). Removable, anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed, washable at up to 30°C Material: PU (polyurethane) Footbed lining: suede Sole: PU (polyurethane), nonslip, oil- and grease-resistant Certified occupational footwear in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 OB E (SRC category) A630 / A640 Replacement Footbed Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Arizona ESD
description: With its high level of comfort and the anatomically shaped original cork-latex footbed, the Arizona two-strap sandal from BIRKENSTOCK lends itself well to daily occupational use. Thanks to its additional ESD properties to combat spontaneous electrostatic discharge, this model is ideal for wearing in ESD areas. The combination of the footbed and the specially developed sole guarantees permanently gentle discharge and protects sensitive parts. All BIRKENSTOCK ESD models are tested in accordance with the requirements of EN 61340 and meet the ESD requirements of 1.0 × 105 to 3.5 × 107 ohms. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed in an ESD version Upper: Birko-Flor® Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckles Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA outsole in an ESD version ESD protection tested in accordance with EN 61340 Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Boston ESD
description: The Boston ESD offers the ideal combination of classic looks and reliable protection from electrostatic discharge. The ESD version therefore protects man and materials in highly sensitive areas like in the semiconductor industry. All BIRKENSTOCK ESD models are tested in accordance with the requirements of EN 61340 and meet the ESD requirements of 1.0 × 105 to 3.5 × 107 ohms. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed in an ESD version Upper: smooth leather Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckle Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA outsole in an ESD version ESD protection tested in accordance with EN 61340 The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Catalina BS
description: The design of the BIRKENSTOCK Catalina was inspired by the classic Madrid with a strap and metal buckle. The slightly wider strap lends this sandal a modern elegant appearance. This version comes in a shiny lizard design and exudes elegance and a touch of extravagance thanks to the iridescent metallic foil and the reptile skin look. Inspired by nature, no two shoes have the same look and feel. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®, which has been embossed. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: embossed Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: strap with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle Made in Germany Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Florida Flex Platform
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Florida is the ideal sandal for anyone who spends a lot of time on their feet. This three-strap sandal offers good grip and maximum comfort. The new platform flex outsole has a wider heel section for increased stability and ideal weight distribution. The updated design with horizontal grooves in the front part improves flexibility and the rolling motion. Modeled on the cork original, this sandal is made from especially light and highly flexible EVA. This high-quality, odor-neutral synthetic material which has been tested for harmful substances is shock-absorbent, water-resistant, and skin-friendly. It is therefore perfect for wearing on the beach, in the garden, or in wellness and spa areas. Anatomically shaped BIRKENSTOCK footbed made from EVA Upper/footbed lining/sole: a single piece of EVA Details: water-resistant, washable, ultra-lightweight Made in Germany EVA (ethylene vinyl acetate) is a high-quality, very light, elastic material with very good cushioning. As a result, it smooths out slight irregularities in the floor and ensures that every step is softly cushioned.

Birko-Flor – durable, synthetic upper material with leather-like finish and soft backing Contoured cork footbed conforms to the shape of your foot and features pronounced arch support, a deep heel cup, and roomy toe box; lined with suede Lightweight EVA sole for cushioning and shock absorption Avoid extreme heat Heel shape: flat “Made in Germany” Birko-Flor® Patent is made from our easy-to-care-for, moisture-repellent synthetic material Birko-Flor® with a patent finish. It is bright, gaudy and radiant. There is no end to the choice of colours.

title: Kay Kids
description: A comfy all-rounder! The BIRKENSTOCK Kay clog can be worn flexibly and offers additional grip at the heel if needed. Here, we see the sandal with a silky sheen finish. The color-coordinated footbed rounds off the shoe’s look of sophistication. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. The Kay clog is therefore a suitable model for active kids – there’s little chance of shoes getting lost. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle – one of which can be folded back and used as an ankle strap; color-coordinated footbed Made in Germany Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Kay PRO
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Kay Pro clog boasts two straps, one of which is fixed firmly to the shaft. Thanks to the hidden rivet on the side, the second strap can be folded back and, if necessary, can either be worn on the shaft or as an ankle strap for extra grip. This version stands out in particular with its light polyurethane sole. It is nonslip, allows for a dynamic foot rolling motion, and can also be repaired. The upper is made from high-quality, particularly soft natural leather which is coated with polyurethane (PU). The PU coating makes the material vapor-permeable and regulates the climate in the clog. Original BIRKENSTOCK soft footbed; anatomically shaped Upper: PU-coated natural leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: light polyurethane (PU) sole Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle – one which can be folded back and worn as an ankle strap Tested in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2022 The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: Kay SL
description: The Kay Super Grip offers all the advantages of BIRKENSTOCK’s classic Tokio and Boston models in one. The upper instep strap can be folded back if required, thus providing additional support as a backstrap. The Super Grip sole is nonslip, promotes the ideal rolling motion, and is also oil- and grease-resistant. Its midsole made from EVA cushions every step. This high degree of flexibility and sure-footedness is in great demand in particular in medical environments. All Super Grip soles are tested for slip resistance in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Details: individually adjustable metal pin buckle Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA midsole with nonslip, oil- and grease-resistant rubber outsole Slip resistance tested in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 (SRA category) Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Mogami Terra Stealth
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Mogami Terra is the perfect match for adventures of any kind thanks to the water-resistant footbed with toe protection and the highly functional sole which is injected into the footbed and upper in two layers. title: Oita
description: The casual BIRKENSTOCK Oita takes its inspiration from the classic Kyoto model and stands out with its slim and feminine design and individually adjustable fastener. This offers optimum grip and is complemented by two decorative rivets. The upper is made from especially soft suede, which hugs the foot like a second skin, combined with high-quality nubuck leather. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede; nubuck leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: individually adjustable fastener; decorative rivets “Made in Germany” Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: QO 400
description: BIRKENSTOCK’s QO400 work shoe with a removable footbed offers firm grip and takes the strain off your feet, allowing you to stand and move around comfortably at work for many hours, even in demanding environments. The QO400 has no lacing and is presented as a simple slip-on shoe. The nonslip and oil- and petrol-resistant outsole provides for energy absorption around the heel. The upper is made from water-resistant smooth leather (WRU) and offers antistatic protection. The shoe is certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 and meets the requirements of protection category O2. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

The shoe is certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 and meets the requirements of protection category O2. title: Rio Kids
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Rio model is a classic kids’ shoe. Designed back in the 1970s, it has been a laid-back summer companion for generations of children ever since. BIRKENSTOCK has reinterpreted the Rio sandal in stylish neon colors and high-quality synthetic material. Modeled on the cork sandal, it is made from the ultra lightweight and highly flexible synthetic material EVA. Anatomically shaped BIRKENSTOCK footbed in EVA Upper/lining/sole: one-piece EVA Details: shoe molded from a single piece, metal buckle, waterproof, washable, shock-absorbent, ultra lightweight “Made in Germany” EVA (ethylene vinyl acetate) is a high-quality, very light, elastic material with very good cushioning. As a result, it smooths out slight irregularities in the floor and ensures that every step is softly cushioned.

title: Super-Birki
description: The wide array of colors that the Super Birki is available in makes it highly versatile for use in all sorts of occupational and private settings. This compact shoe made from water-resistant and dirt-repellent polyurethane is also oil- and grease-resistant. This extremely resilient material is washable at up to 60° Celsius and can be efficiently disinfected. Its resilience and its hygiene properties make it ideal for kitchens, medical environments, and the food industry – while it can equally serve as a practical garden clog. The anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed is lined with a moisture-wicking fabric. It can be removed for easy cleaning and is washable at up to 30° Celsius. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed, washable at up to 30°C Material: PU (polyurethane) Footbed lining: fabric Sole: PU (polyurethane), oil- and grease-resistant Super Birki Replacement Footbed Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Utti Lace
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Utti is a timeless moccasin-style shoe. The striking stitching catches the eye. The soft heel tab not only guarantees comfort but also ensures that the shoe is easy to put on and take off. Original BIRKENSTOCK Deep Blue Footbed; anatomically shaped and removable Upper: suede Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: natural rubber with cork elements Details: moccasin with striking stitching and heel tab Footbed: made in Germany Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Almina
description: The Almina sandal from Papillio is a platform sandal with a with a slight, flared wedge heel. Its optimum stability thanks to the wide strap at the instep makes it a real hit with women who want both high fashion and comfort. The upper is made from high-quality, soft nubuck leather that boasts a natural, rustic appearance. title: Colorado Kids
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Colorado is a variation on the classic Rio. The buckle at the ankle strap has been replaced by a hook-and-loop fastener, allowing it to be put on and taken off in an instant – perfect for kids’ impatient feet! This popular sandal has been given an update in a new material, with a vegan version now available. It is entirely free of animal products, as verified by independent testing laboratories. The BIRKENSTOCK Mogami is the perfect match for adventures of any kind thanks to the waterproof footbed with toe protection and the highly functional sole which is injected into the footbed and upper in two layers. This makes the sandal extremely flexible and durable in any terrain. This version boasts vibrant colors. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. Anatomically shaped footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: polyurethane (PU) Sole: polyurethane (PU) Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable pin buckle; ankle strap Made in Germany Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Oswego
description: Just slip in! The BIRKENSTOCK Oswego is a handy slip-on shoe that will delight both men and women alike. The casual low shoe features elastic inserts which make it easy to put it on and take it off in no time. The flexible rubber sole with a shock-absorbing cork-PU intermediate layer and the padding at the edge of the shaft result in even more comfort. The upper is made from especially soft suede which hugs the foot like a second skin. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede Footbed lining: suede Sole: made of natural rubber Footbed “Made in Germany” Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Profi-Birki
description: BIRKENSTOCK developed the Profi Birki to offer perfect grip and sure-footedness in almost any work environment. With its raised heel section and extended front, it encloses the entire foot and promotes a natural rolling motion with every step you take. The Profi Birki is a top choice among long-term employees in hospitals, the food industry, and kitchens. Its outstanding hygiene properties likewise attest to this: the oil- and grease-resistant clog is washable at up to 80° Celsius, while the removable PU footbed can be washed at up to 60° Celsius and can also be disinfected. Removable, anatomically shaped PU footbed, washable at up to 60°C Material: PU (polyurethane) Footbed lining: fabric Sole: PU (polyurethane), oil- and grease-resistant Profi Birki Replacement Footbed Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Zermatt Kids
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Zermatt is our first slipper with a removable footbed, allowing you to choose between three different insoles. You can choose from the Standard Footbed, the Soft Footbed and the Shearling Footbed. All three insoles can be ordered separately. Perfect for all year round! This basic version of this design features our Standard Footbed. It replicates the natural print made by a foot walking on sand and will see you through the day in comfort. The upper is made from soft wool felt. With adjustable straps and a magical cork footbed that conforms to the shape of your foot, a truly custom fit is as effortless as the classic design. “Made in Germany” Birkibuc – a durable, synthetic upper material with a nubuck leather-like texture and a soft backing Contoured cork footbed conforms to the shape of your foot and features pronounced arch support, a deep heel cup, and roomy toe box; lined with suede Lightweight EVA sole for cushioning and shock absorption Avoid extreme heat The look and feel of Birko-Flor® Nubuck is an almost perfect imitation of authentic nubuck leather.

title: Arizona Crosstown
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Arizona is a genuine classic that has been delighting both men and women with its timeless design for decades. This version is designed for BIRKENSTOCK fans who are active and looking for an experience. The polyurethane sole is affixed to the footbed in two layers and therefore offers maximum flexibility, grip and durability. The upper is made from extra thick, oiled nubuck leather with an open-selvage finish. Oiled leather is one of our favourite types of leather. Its oily waxed surface makes for a unique colour effect and develops a beautiful patina. The oily finish of our natural leather products results in colour variation, making each and every pair unique.

title: Arizona ESD
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Arizona is a genuine classic that has been delighting both men and women for decades. This simple sandal with two straps stands for timeless design and is also perfect for daily use at work thanks to its comfort factor. Due to its additional ESD properties to combat spontaneous electrostatic discharge, this model is ideal for wearing in ESD areas. The combination of the footbed and the specially developed sole guarantees permanently gentle discharge and protects sensitive parts. All BIRKENSTOCK ESD models are tested in accordance with the requirements of DIN EN 61340 and meet the ESD requirements of 1.0 × 105 to 3.5 × 107 ohms. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed in an ESD version Upper: Birko-Flor® Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle Footbed lining: suede Sole: cushioning EVA outsole in an ESD version ESD protection tested in accordance with EN 61340 Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Mogami Terra Stealth
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Mogami Terra is the perfect match for adventures of any kind thanks to the water-resistant footbed with toe protection and the highly functional sole which is injected into the footbed and upper in two layers. This makes the sandal extremely flexible and durable in any terrain. The polyurethane sole is affixed to the footbed in two layers and therefore offers maximum flexibility, grip, and durability. This version has two straps featuring the modern and functional BIRKENSTOCK stealth buckle. Made from a stainless synthetic material, this buckle is not only durable, but also boasts minimalist design. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. Anatomically shaped footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: polyurethane (PU) Sole: light polyurethane (PU) sole Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable synthetic pin buckle Made in Germany Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Kay
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Kay clog boasts two straps, one of which is fixed firmly to the shaft. Thanks to the hidden stud on the side, the second strap can be folded back and, if necessary, can either be worn on the shaft or as an ankle strap for extra grip. This ESD version was developed specifically for people working in microelectronics or with high-frequency technology. ESD stands for “electrostatic discharge". These shoe models continuously discharge their wearers gently. The antistatic elements in the sole balance out potential differences between the electrical charge of the wearer and their work environment by permanently “grounding" the feet and can be identified by a round, yellow emblem. Warning: the ESD range goes up to values of 34 Mohm and is therefore non-insulating! The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor®. The shoe has been tested in accordance with EN ISO 61340. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA with electrostatic discharge (ESD) Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle Tested in accordance with EN ISO 61340 Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

Here, the model comes with a special detail: the straps have a braided pattern, making them the perfect match for fashionable boho styles. The upper is made from especially soft suede which hugs the foot like a second skin. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: one strap with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle Made in Germany Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Recovery Pack
description:
Our Recovery Set offers the perfect combination of support, comfort and massage to relieve and revitalize your feet. The set consists of the innovative Active Recovery footbed, the Birki Air 2.0 in a special colorway and a three-piece foot massage set.

The Active Recovery footbed is designed to stimulate specific trigger points in the foot reflex zones. These trigger points are integrated into the footbed which is based on BIRKENSTOCK’s signature anatomical design. For added comfort and hygiene, the footbed is replaceable and fits the entire clog range. Made from durable PU, the insole is both abrasion-resistant and of optimum hardness. Raised nubs on the surface promote blood circulation and thus contribute to the health of the feet.
 Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Super-Birki Shearling
description: The Super Birki has long since become a model which is not only perfect for gardening or work but which is also a popular choice for your leisure time. With its flat heel section, this seamless clog provides the feet with all-around protection and grip. This is a particularly cozy version with shearling lining. The upper is made of polyurethane (PU). It is flexible, water- and dirt-repellent and makes the shoe particularly easy to care for. Anatomically shaped footbed Upper: polyurethane (PU) Footbed lining: shearling Sole: polyurethane (PU) Details: flexible, water- and dirt-repellent “Made in Germany” Polyurethane, also known as PU, is a synthetic material ideally suited for use outdoors. The material is water-repellent and dirt-resistant and extremely easy to care for.

title: Zermatt
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Zermatt is our first slipper with a removable footbed, allowing you to choose between two different insoles. You can choose from the Standard Footbed and the Shearling Footbed. The insoles can be ordered separately. Perfect for all year round! This basic version of this design features our Standard Footbed. It replicates the natural print made by a foot walking on sand and will see you through the day in comfort. The upper is made from soft wool felt. Our model (f) wears the narrow width. Our model (m) wears the regular width. Wool felt counts among the oldest textile materials in the world and is the typical upper material for slippers.

title: Zermatt Premium Suede LEA Sole
description: Slip it on for instant well-being and snugness! The BIRKENSTOCK Zermatt is our first slipper with a removable footbed, allowing you to choose between three different insoles. The classic is now available in a particularly cozy premium design. Its natural design is down to the upper made from especially soft suede, which hugs the foot like a second skin. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: clog with extended shaft; decorative stitching; decorative rivet Footbed “Made in Germany” Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Gizeh Big Buckle
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Gizeh is a genuine classic that combines optimum grip with minimalist, fashionable design. The Big Buckle version features a large, elegant pin buckle – a fantastic, striking eye-catcher on this otherwise understated sandal. The lining of the semi-exquisite footbed is covered with soft smooth leather and matches the shoe in color. The upper is made from extra thick, oiled nubuck leather and features an open-selvage finish. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed; semi-exquisite Upper: natural leather Footbed lining: oiled nubuck leather Sole: EVA Details: thong with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle “Made in Germany” Oiled leather is one of our favourite types of leather. Its oily waxed surface makes for a unique colour effect and develops a beautiful patina. The oily finish of our natural leather products results in colour variation, making each and every pair unique.

title: Ramses

The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor® in a sophisticated nubuck look which boasts a texture and color that could almost be mistaken for real leather. title: Birmingham Lace Women
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Birmingham Lace is a rustic lace-up boot. The robust rubber outsole ensures a secure grip and can be repaired when worn down. The comfortable and light Deep Blue Footbed makes the shoe a perfect 24/7 all-rounder, especially on long and active days. Perfect for your next holiday, extensive walks or city trips. The classic is now available as a premium version with a leather runner board and striking stitching. The runner board constitutes the substructure of the footbed and is not visible. The upper is made from exceptionally high-quality Horween cowhide which was initially developed for use in professional sports. Original BIRKENSTOCK Deep Blue Footbed; anatomically shaped and removable Upper: natural Horween leather Footbed lining: microfiber Runner board: natural leather Sole: natural rubber Footbed “Made in Germany” Oiled leather is one of our favourite types of leather. Its oily waxed surface makes for a unique colour effect and develops a beautiful patina. The oily finish of our natural leather products results in colour variation, making each and every pair unique.

title: QO 700
description: BIRKENSTOCK’s QO700 work shoe with a removable footbed offers firm grip and takes the strain off your feet, allowing you to stand and move around comfortably at work for many hours, even in demanding environments. The QO700 is presented as a modern, ankle-high sneaker with 7-hole lacing and a heel loop. The nonslip and oil- and petrol-resistant outsole provides for energy absorption around the heel. The upper is made from water-resistant microfiber (WRU) and offers antistatic protection. The shoe is certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 and meets the requirements of protection category O2. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-microfiber footbed Material: water-resistant microfiber (WRU) Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: nitrile rubber (SRC) Details: nonslip and oil- and petrol-resistant outsole (SRC, FO); energy absorption around heel (E); antistatic protection (A) Work shoe certified in accordance with EN ISO 20347:2012 Protection category O2 Replacement Footbed QO / QS women Replacement Footbed QO / QS men Microfibers are a very fine synthetic fibers that are extremely soft and shape-retentive. As with Birko-Flor® the surface is combined with a layer of breathable fleece.

title: QS 500 ESD
description: BIRKENSTOCK’s QS500 safety shoe with a removable footbed offers firm grip and takes the strain off your feet, allowing you to stand and move around comfortably at work for many hours, even in demanding environments. The QS500 is presented as a simple, modern sneaker with 6-hole lacing. This ESD version was developed specifically for people working in microelectronics or with high-frequency technology. ESD stands for “electrostatic discharge". These shoe models continuously discharge their wearers gently. The antistatic elements in the sole balance out potential differences between the electrical charge of the wearer and their work environment by permanently “grounding" the feet and can be identified by a round, yellow emblem. Warning: the ESD range goes up to values of 35 Mohm and is therefore non-insulating! The nonslip, metal-free, and oil- and petrol-resistant outsole additionally provides for energy absorption around the heel and is penetration-resistant. A 200-joule steel toe with a scratch-resistant toe cap protects the forefoot. The upper is made from water-resistant smooth leather (WRU) and offers antistatic protection. The shoe is certified in accordance with EN ISO 20345:2011 and meets the requirements of protection category S3. Removable, anatomically shaped cork-microfiber footbed Material: water-resistant smooth leather (WRU) Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: nitrile rubber (SRC) Details: steel toe (200 joules) with scratch-resistant toe cap; penetration-resistant, metal-free, nonslip, and oil- and petrol-resistant outsole (P, SRC, FO); energy absorption around heel (E); ESD protection (A) Safety shoe certified in accordance with EN ISO 20345:2011 Protection category S3 Replacement Footbed QO / QS women Replacement Footbed QO / QS men The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

title: 250 Anniversary Edition Blue Footbed
description: Enjoy the footbed feeling in almost every shoe! Our Blue Footbed is designed to support the natural shape of your foot, with distinct arch supports and a deep heel cup that provides the support you’ve come to know and love from our classic footbed. Thin, light and flexible, the Blue Footbed takes up minimal space in your shoe and promotes a healthy alignment for all foot types. title: Blue Footbed for Sneakers

title: Arizona Vegan
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Arizona is a genuine classic that has been delighting both men and women with its timeless design for decades. The color-coordinated outsole rounds off the shoe’s look of sophistication. This classic model has been given an update in a new material, with a vegan version now available. It is entirely free of animal products, as verified by independent testing laboratories. The upper is made from a skin-friendly synthetic material. The sandal boasts sophisticated material use with a matte finish that’s reminiscent of natural leather while nevertheless being 100% vegan. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: synthetic material Footbed lining: microfiber Sole: EVA Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle; vegan; color-coordinated outsole “Made in Germany” Our synthetic material is a fabric made of synthetic fibres and is used in various versions for the production of our shoes. It is skin-friendly and durable.

title: Kyoto

The upper is made from high-quality, soft nubuck leather that boasts a rustic appearance. title: Arizona Shearling
description: The bolder, the better! This is a wonderfully comfy version of the classic BIRKENSTOCK Arizona model with shearling footbed lining and straps lined with lambskin. The sandal can be individually adjusted to the wearer’s feet using the two metal pin buckles in a vintage look. This ensures an excellent fit and firm grip. The comfort level is boosted by the flexible EVA outsole with signature BIRKENSTOCK bone profile, which enables a healthy rolling motion. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: suede Footbed lining: shearling Sole: EVA Details: two straps, each with an adjustable metal pin buckle “Made in Germany” Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity. Suede is softer and more flexible by nature and does not have the same stability as smooth leather. The stability of suede also varies from hide to hide. This does not constitute a material or production defect.

title: Atacama Men
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Atacama is a variation on the classic Arizona and is the perfect sandal for anyone who is on their feet all day. The pin buckles have been replaced by hook-and-loop fasteners and the heel of the sole has been reinforced. Perfect for all active and adventurous BIRKENSTOCK fans. The polyurethane sole is affixed to the footbed in two layers and therefore offers maximum flexibility, grip and durability. The upper is made from the skin-friendly, hard-wearing synthetic material Birko-Flor® which was reinterpreted with a futuristic look. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Futura Footbed lining: polyurethane (PU) Sole: light polyurethane sole (PU) Details: two straps, each with an individually adjustable hook-and-loop fastener “Made in Germany” Birko-Flor® is a skin-friendly, tear-resistant and easy-to-care-for synthetic material which is exclusively used by BIRKENSTOCK.

title: Boston Bold
description: The BIRKENSTOCK Boston clog is a veritable classic that can easily be worn all year round and offers support and protection for kids’ feet. This version is modern and urban. It boasts an upper made from aniline leather with a natural grain complemented by a brass buckle. Thanks to its two components, the sole promotes stability and comfort. It comprises a cushioning midsole made from EVA and an outsole made from genuine rubber and rounds off the sophisticated, uniform look. Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: aniline leather Footbed lining: suede Sole: rubber-EVA sole Details: strap with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle “Made in Germany” The natural leather that we use is mostly smooth leather, in some cases tumbled leather. This type of leather has many special characteristics, such as breathability, adaptation to the shape of the foot and durability.

Anatomically shaped cork-latex footbed Upper: Birko-Flor® Footbed lining: suede Sole: EVA Details: one strap and an ankle strap, each with an individually adjustable metal pin buckle; color-coordinated footbed Made in Germany Birko-Flor® Patent is made from our easy-to-care-for, moisture-repellent synthetic material Birko-Flor® with a patent finish. It is bright, gaudy and radiant. There is no end to the choice of colours.

title: Arizona Rivets
description: An icon of timeless design and legendary comfort, the Arizona sandal has been defining style since 1973. Metallic rivets stud its classic suede upper, thoughtfully placed to leave the underside smooth. On an original contoured footbed, you'll feel comfortable standing out from the rest. Contoured cork-latex footbed creates custom support with wear Suede upper with metallic rivets Suede footbed lining helps keep you comfortable Flexible EVA sole Two straps with adjustable metal pin buckles Made in Germany Suede is a split leather with a napped finish. It has a velvety surface and is very soft to the touch. It also boasts a high moisture absorption capacity.
